OL,6,F"To try and turn an investigation of a
OL,7,Fsuspect into a chance to blackmail
OL,8,Fthem out of money is disgraceful, and
OL,9,Fthen to falsify police reports to
OL,10,Fcover her tracks is reprehensible.
OL,12,F"The fact that blackmail is a serious
OL,13,Fcrime, no matter who the victim is or
OL,14,Fwhat they have done, should have been
OL,15,Fobvious to anyone, especially a police
OL,16,Fofficer.
OL,18,F"Her conduct amounted to a serious
OL,19,Fabuse of the trust which we rightly
OL,20,Fhave in anyone in public office to
OL,21,Fperform their duties."
